{
  "doc_id": "30452",
  "text": "It is well documented that MCI subjects are at an increased risk of acquiring AD, and around 10-15% of these subjects convert to AD on a yearly basis [CITATION_1] . By stratifying MCI individuals to MCI-c and MCI-nc, we found significantly diminished baseline CSF MTf levels in the former group. Indeed, lower CSF MTf were associated with greater cognitive deficits (ADAS-Cog13) in MCI and lower hippocampal volumes in both CN and MCI. While not associated with hippocampal volume, CSF MTf was associated with longitudinal hippocampal volume change in AD. MTf appears to have a role in mediating cellular iron uptake [CITATION_2] , and hence likely to be involved in iron metabolism.",
